Introduction

FIFTY FIFTY is a South Korean girl group formed by ATTRAKT who debuted on November 18, 2022, with their mini album "THE FIFTY". The group’s name symbolizes a 50:50 balance between ideal and reality. They received critical acclaim early on, with IZM awarding them a 4.5-star rating, and the Grammys recognizing them as one of the top girl groups to watch in 2023. Their single "Cupid" became a global hit, especially after a TikTok viral moment, leading to chart success, including on the Billboard Hot 100 and UK Singles Chart.

In April 2023, ATTRAKT partnered with Warner Records for U.S. promotions. However, in June 2023, Aran went on hiatus to recover from surgery. Shortly after, ATTRAKT revealed issues of “outside forces” poaching the group. This was later on revealed to be ATTRAKT’s partner, The Givers, trying to get the group to join Warner Music Korea effectively violating the group’s contract.

Later on, FIFTY FIFTY sued ATTRAKT to cancel their contracts, citing contract breaches and reputation damage as the reason. By August, talks failed, leading back to court. On October 23, ATTRAKT officially ended their exclusive agreements with Saena, Sio, and Aran, effective from October 19, while Keena had withdrawn her appeal for injunction. The following day, the Seoul High Court dismissed an appeal from the three artists to suspend their contracts.

In 2024, ATTRAKT began reorganizing the group with Keena and introduced four new members: Chanelle Moon, Yewon, Hana and Athena. On August 30, the group released the song "Starry Night", marking a new beginning for them.
